Title : Portal:Current events/2014 April 27
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|04|27}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[Post-coup unrest in Egypt (2013–14)|Post-coup unrest in Egypt]]:
**An [[Egypt|Egyptian]] court sentences 11 supporters of deposed President [[Mohammed Morsi]] to prison terms ranging from five to 88 years for rioting.[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-27176608 (BBC)]
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]:
**Pro-[[Russia|Russian]] rebels in [[Ukraine]] free a [[Sweden|Swedish]] observer, but not the other seven [[Europe|European]] monitors they have been holding for three days.[https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/27/us-ukraine-crisis-idUSBREA3O16720140427 (BBC)]
*[[Iraq|Iraqi]] helicopters destroy a convoy of [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] fuel tankers inside [[Syrian]] territory.[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-27179916 (BBC)]

;Arts and culture
*[[Canonization of Pope John XXIII and Pope John Paul II]]:
**Popes [[Pope John XXIII|John XXIII]] and [[Pope John Paul II|John Paul II]] are declared [[Sainthood|saints]] by [[Pope Francis]] in the first papal canonization since 1954. [http://time.com/78080/pope-canonization-preparation/ (''Time'')] [http://edition.cnn.com/2014/04/27/world/pope-canonization/?hpt=hp_t2 (CNN)]

;Disasters and accidents
*Eight people are killed by a fire in a medical facility in [[Russia]]'s eastern [[Altai Republic|Altai]] region.[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27177661 (BBC)]
*[[Tornado outbreak of April 27–30, 2014]]:
**At least two people are killed after a [[tornado]] touches down in [[Quapaw, Oklahoma]], United States. [http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/official-dead-tornado-hits-quapaw-oklahoma-extent-damage-23491872 (ABC News)]
**Tornadoes hit the [[Arkansas]] towns of [[Vilonia, Arkansas|Vilonia]] and [[Mayflower, Arkansas|Mayflower]] with reports of casualties. [http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-04-28/reports-of-mass-casualties-as-tornadoes-hit-us/5415536 (Reuters via ABC News Australia)]

;Health
*[[Middle East respiratory syndrome]]:
**[[Saudi Arabia]] reports eight more deaths and 16 more cases in the latest outbreak of the disease. [https://news.yahoo.com/saudi-arabia-reports-8-more-deaths-mers-virus-201548044.html (AP via Yahoo! News)]

;Politics and elections
*[[Sinking of the MV Sewol|Sinking of the MV ''Sewol'']]
**The [[Prime Minister of South Korea]] [[Jung Hong-won]] announces his immediate resignation following growing criticism of the response to the sinking of the MV ''Sewol''. [http://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia-pacific/2014/04/south-korea-pm-resigns-over-ferry-disaster-201442703119736746.html (Al-Jazeera)]

